  "title": "Senior Cybersecurity Operations Specialist",
  "description": "<p><strong>Role: Senior Cybersecurity Operations Specialist</strong></p><p><strong>Location: Singapore</strong></p><p><strong>We are partnering with a leading telecom client </strong>to hire a Cybersecurity Operations Specialist who will support, troubleshoot, and operate critical security systems in a fast-paced enterprise environment.<br /></p><p>Responsibilities:</p><ul><li>Provide L1/L2 support for security tools (Firewalls, WAF, EDR, VPN, Email/Web Security, DLP, IAM)<br /></li><li>Monitor, maintain, and optimize security platforms for performance and reliability<br /></li><li>Support security incident triage, investigation, and resolution (MTTD / MTTR focus)<br /></li><li>Perform system patching, tuning, integrations, and lifecycle management<br /></li><li>Work closely with SOC, IT, Network, and vendors to ensure smooth security operations<br /></li></ul><h3>Requirements</h3><ul><li>6–10 years of experience in Cybersecurity Operations / Security Engineering<br /></li><li>Strong hands-on experience with enterprise security tools<br /></li><li>Good understanding of networking, security controls, and incident handling<br /></li><li>Experience in regulated / large-scale environments (Telecom, BFSI, Tech preferred)<br /></li><li>Relevant security certifications (Cisco, Palo Alto, Fortinet, Microsoft Security - nice to have)</li></ul><p><br /><em>UEN: 202329526G</em></p><p><em>EA Licence: 23S2061</em></p>",
